@node MAIN "acknowledgements.html"
     Acknowledgements     Acknowledgements  

Another version, another completely changed acknowledgements list ;)  

A lot of the impetus of Tag-o-Miga has tailed off in recent years, due to the declining Amiga Fidonet scene, where most of the initial development took place. This is the reason why this version has been so long coming, for relatively little improvements.  

The full acknowledgements list looks like:       
    	
    All the friends I've made in Halls of Residence this year         -- my second year didn't go well but you put the spring         back in my step again, so I can honestly say my third         year has been the best of my time at University. Cheers!     
    	
    Simon Avery, sysop of Digital Dilemma BBS (and N2:255C!)         Tag-o-Miga was inspired by Simon's DOS program         Tag-o-Matic, and now that Tag-o-Miga has a PC version,         it's come full circle. Simon is my Fidonet boss and his         BBS is the official Fidonet distribution site of         Tag-o-Miga and Frontier Town Software.     
    	
    Ian, James, Chandy, Jon and all the other DCS dudes B-)     
    	
    My future employer (I know who they are now but it's not         confirmed so I'll keep quiet for now!) Good grief, I'm         actually going to start **earning** money soon!     
    	
    James Lowe, for some bug reports and AmiTag (a handy         little program for adding taglines to tagfiles - an ideal         counterpart to Tag-o-Miga!)     
    	
    All the users of Tag-o-Miga. You're the reason why I'm         making this version.   
	----------------------------------------
  

&quot;Blood, sweat and tears really don't matter, just to think that you've been in this garden.&quot;
 &nbsp; -- Levellers, &quot;This Garden&quot;   
 
@endnode

